{"name": "dllist", "metadata": {"name": "dllist", "version": "1.2.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: System", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": null, "license": "BSD-3-Clause", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "List the shared libraries loaded by the current process.", "upload_time": 1715718339}, "documentation": ["# dllist\n\nA very small Python library to list the DLLs loaded by the current process.\nThis is equivalent to the [`dllist`](https://docs.julialang.org/en/v1/stdlib/Libdl/#Base.Libc.Libdl.dllist) function in Julia.\n\n*Note*: This library is tested on macOS, Linux, and Windows.\n\nSome platforms which provide the same API as Linux (e.g. FreeBSD) may also work.\n\nAny other platform will return an empty list and raise a warning.\n\n## Installation\n\n`dllist` is [available on PyPI](https://pypi.org/project/dllist/):\n\n```\npip install dllist\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nimport dllist\nprint(dllist.dllist())\n# ['linux-vdso.so.1', '/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libpthread.so.0', '/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libdl.so.2', ...\n```\n\n*Note*: The library paths are not postprocessed by this library. Depending on your usage, you may need to convert them to absolute paths and/or perform case-normalization (Windows).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "dllist.macos", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dllist.macos._platform_specific_dllist", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/System/Conceptual/ManPages_iPhoneOS/man3/dyld.3.html"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dllist", "documentation": ["A reimplementation of Julia's dllist"], "functions": [{"name": "dllist._platform_specific_dllist", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dllist.dllist", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["List the dynamic libraries loaded by the current process.\n\nThis is a wrapper for platform-specific APIs on Windows, Linux, and macOS.\nOn other platforms, this function will return an empty list.\n\nReturns\n-------\nList[str]\n    The names of the dynamic libraries loaded by the current process."]}], "variables": [{"name": "dllist.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dllist._system", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "dllist._platform_specific_dllist", "xref": {"fqname": "dllist.unix_like._platform_specific_dllist", "project": null}}, {"name": "dllist._platform_specific_dllist", "xref": {"fqname": "dllist.macos._platform_specific_dllist", "project": null}}, {"name": "dllist._platform_specific_dllist", "xref": {"fqname": "dllist.windows._platform_specific_dllist", "project": null}}, {"name": "dllist.List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "dllist.unix_like", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dllist.unix_like.info_callback", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "info", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "_size", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dllist.unix_like._platform_specific_dllist", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "proj